Throwback to our great trip to Italy.  Thanks again for @firenzeyesplease for arranging the best trip ever.  She booked us dinner at the beautiful #belmondvillasanmichele with a breathtaking view of Florence. During our pre dinner cocktail we got the pleasure to crash a wedding party.  We actually didn’t crash the wedding, they sort of placed themselves around us, and asked us to stay. The wedding was a mix of British and Austrian and Italian flavor.  I love the reaction of the kids, it was an unexpected surprise in a trip filled with tremendous surprises. -

A beautiful unfiltered picture from our visit to Berlin last summer. This is the beautiful Berliner Dom, which had been the royal church and was rebuilt numerous times. The current look dates from 1893.  Much of  the roof and the windows were destroyed in 1944. A partial restoration was finished in 1993. But the East German government also demolished the northern wing that had been untouched by the bombings. They spent more on the demolition 800,000 marks than the restoration 50,000 marks.
